    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600 Models
        Built Before 05/20/2003 - FANS AND ENGINE ACCESSORIES - ETHER START
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ETHER START</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <figure id="f0825521" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0825521.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Ether Start Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 10 AMP (F33) FUSE BLOCK #3 (1013) IN CAB POWER DISTRIBUTION CENTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. (8400) ETHER START</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. (1010) ETHER START SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ETHER BOTTLE CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. (6550) THERMAL SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>When the ether start system is activated a measured amount of ether will be injected into the engine
                intake. This will assist starting the engine during cold weather.
            </para>
            <para>The system will only function if engine temperature is less than 4.4&#176;C (40&#176;F).</para>
            <para>The ether bottle control valve is directly controlled by the ether start switch on the instrument
                panel. A thermal switch will prevent the valve from activating when the temperature is too high.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
